<font color="#FF0000">REALITY?</font><br>
<tt>Sun May 11  9:36:58 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
REALITY?<br>
It seems funny there hasn't been any discussion on Vietnam <br>
Veterans dealings with todays employment environment, as in<br>
dealing with downsizing and re-engineering.  I spent two back<br>
to back tours in the Central Highlands with a heavy artillery<br>
battalion.  As all veterans that survived, I endured. We all<br>
came home scarred.  We put the war behind us and tried to <br>
fit in and do our part in society.  Tomorrow, May 12 1996, I <br>
face the likelyhood of being severed from a job I have had<br>
for 27 years.  I would like to think that I will survive this<br>
ordeal.  I find myself thinking that it all boils down to <br>
money, and greed, then I also reference this with the war!<br>
after all when you talk of the Military Industrial Complex<br>
of the sixties, nothing much has changed, has it?<br>

<p><code>-- TCARTER389@AOL.COM  (Terry Carter) </code><p>


